  <p>
    <app>Hexkudo</app> is number-placement logic game.
    Each puzzle gives you a grid of hexagons and a few numbers as anchor.
    You job is to form a path with consecutive numbers.
    There is only one possible path, which must go through all the cells.
    Consecutive numbers must be adjacent and the diamond shape between two cells is a hint: the two cells have consecutive numbers.
  </p>

  <p>Play the game on screen, or <link xref="index#print">print</link> the puzzles.</p>
  <p>If you do not have time to finish a game, you can <link xref="save-resume">resume</link> it at any time.</p>

